      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Again, if the attacker has that kind access to the machine that runs bitcoind, he can do lots of other things too. Overwriting the binary is just one. Another is just reading the decrypted keys from RAM, or adding his own keys to the keypool in wallet.dat, making sure change gets sent to him at some point in the future long after he left the machine.",
